<div id="review_197009771" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/197009771" />
    <a title="Lori" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1230817-lori"><img alt="Lori" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329975391p2/1230817.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/197009771?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori" href="/user/show/1230817-lori">Lori</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780399252808" href="/book/show/7648633-from-the-notebooks-of-melanin-sun">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1230817-lori?shelf=ya">ya</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer197009771&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer197009771" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5647178809624715953">This is a YA novel about a 13 year old boy who must deal with a major change in his and his mother&apos;s life. He finds out his mother is gay and is seeing a white woman named Kristin. I thought this was well-written book and was pretty accurate on how a young person might feel and react hearing this news. Melanin Sun likes to write, but I really appreciated the fact that the author didn&apos;t make him into some genius writer or something-- he was just a 14 year old from Brooklyn writing how he feels, s</span>
  <span id="freeText5647178809624715953" style="display:none">This is a YA novel about a 13 year old boy who must deal with a major change in his and his mother's life. He finds out his mother is gay and is seeing a white woman named Kristin. I thought this was well-written book and was pretty accurate on how a young person might feel and react hearing this news. Melanin Sun likes to write, but I really appreciated the fact that the author didn't make him into some genius writer or something-- he was just a 14 year old from Brooklyn writing how he feels, since he finds it easier to write than to speak (which really hit home!). The ending wasn't all peachy keen either-- Melanin realized his attitude and feelings would need to go through a lot of work, but he realized having family was better than not having any, and the importance of accepting people for who they are. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5647178809624715953" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


