<div id="review_1057534410" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1057534410" />
    <a title="Taylor White" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34639077-taylor-white"><img alt="Taylor White" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1057534410?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Taylor White" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Taylor White" href="/user/show/34639077-taylor-white">Taylor White</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34639077-taylor-white?shelf=november-12">november-12</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1057534410" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15689471273845346083">From the Notebooks of Melanin Sun by Jacqueline Woodson is a Coretta Scott King Award novel. Melanin Sun is a teenager who keeps notebooks of his thoughts about the world. Melanin and his mother only have each other until a secret Melanin&apos;s mother is keeping is revealed to Melanin. This secret drives Melanin and his mother apart. Melanin struggles with how to handle this new information so he writes it all down in his notebooks. Melanin also struggles with what everyone will think of this knew n</span>
  <span id="freeText15689471273845346083" style="display:none">From the Notebooks of Melanin Sun by Jacqueline Woodson is a Coretta Scott King Award novel. Melanin Sun is a teenager who keeps notebooks of his thoughts about the world. Melanin and his mother only have each other until a secret Melanin's mother is keeping is revealed to Melanin. This secret drives Melanin and his mother apart. Melanin struggles with how to handle this new information so he writes it all down in his notebooks. Melanin also struggles with what everyone will think of this knew news about his mother. At the end of the book, somethings changes inside Melanin and he is able to accept the news about his mother. The theme of this book is understanding and accepting. Melanin handles the news at the beginning with much anger and hatred for his mother. After a couple of weeks go by, Melanin is able to accept the new knowledge and have a better understanding of what his future entails. In my future classroom, I would have my middle school students write their thoughts on gay, lesbian, and homosexuals in their journal. Then I would have them read this book and after reading the novel, I would have them go back and see if their view on the subject has changed and why. Hopefully by having discussions over this topic while reading this novel, many students will have a better understanding and accepting mind set than when we began the topic. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15689471273845346083" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


